 Board (FASB) that requires all publicly-traded firms in the United States
 to classify their assets into three categories, Level 1, Level 2, or Level
 3, according to the level of uncertainty with which fair values can be
 determined.
 Based on this, regulators have prescribed the write down of Level 3 assets,
 which are the most illiquid and therefore the highest fair valuation uncertaint
y.
 More details on asset valuation classification can be found in 
